{"id": 72, "ts": 1778753218.4541857, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_2", "message": "After reviewing all available attributes, the decisive factor for a long\u2011distance pilot is **reliable, safe performance over many hours together with the crew**.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** is the only candidate with an explicit statement of being *100\u202f% reliable*. He makes quick, correct decisions, stays calm in crises, and consistently creates a positive crew atmosphere. His excellent attention skills and self\u2011less focus on others directly support sustained crew coordination and safety on long\u2011haul flights.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** shows strong problem\u2011solving, concentration, and responsibility, but we have **no evidence of his overall reliability or track record**, and his \u201cknow\u2011it\u2011all\u201d attitude, hot temper, and weak leadership pose higher risk to crew interaction over extended periods.\n- **Candidate\u202fA** has good situational awareness and leadership, yet lacks any reliability evidence and is described as unorganized, a show\u2011off, and resistant to criticism\u2014serious concerns for long\u2011haul operations.\n- **Candidate\u202fB** is conscientious and handles stress well, but his weak memory for numbers, nasty remarks, and grumpy, uncooperative demeanor undermine teamwork and crew morale; again, no reliability record is provided.\nWhile Candidate\u202fC\u2019s communication difficulty, egocentric reputation, and reluctance for further education are noted, they do not outweigh his proven reliability and crew\u2011supportive behavior, which are paramount for safe, long\u2011distance flights. Therefore, Candidate\u202fC remains the strongest overall fit.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
